Tajikistan's "Avesta" news agency 11th quoted the Tower Central Bank as saying that the first 7 months of this year's inflation rate of 3.7%.
reported that the first 7 months of this year's inflation rate of 3.7%, which July inflation rate of 0.6%, and nearly a year's inflation rate of 6%.
The government's goal is to plan to keep inflation at 7.5% per cent in 2016, compared with 5.1% in 2015, the report said.
In addition, the report points out that there is a certain discrepancy between the tower government and some of the major international financial institutions in the country's economic development and inflation in the 2016.
According to the Ministry of Trade and Economic development, the economic growth of the country in 2016 will be 7%, and the inflation rate of the state is basically above this level.
The Asian Development Bank, the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund have given different forecasts for the 2016 economic development and inflationary waters of the country.
For both indicators, the Asian Development Bank forecasts 4.2% and 7%, the World Bank forecasts 4.8% and 7.5%, and the IMF forecasts 3.4% and 8.2%.
It is reported that despite a series of adverse external factors, such as the international economic downturn, the devaluation of the Russian rouble and the reduction of remittances, the 2015 economic growth of the country was 6%.
